name: cyclobutane, methylene-
Reason: 1,3-butadiene has a melting point of -108.9°C. The basic unit for comparison is cyclobutane, which has a melting point of -120.0°C. The methylene bridge introduces a double bond, which increases the rigidity and molecular weight, thus raising the melting point. The estimated increase due to the methylene bridge is approximately +10°C.
